4 Hours Ago She announced that two witnesses were in court but would not want to proceed in the absence of the lead counsel and sought an adjournment. Her apology did not go down well with the judge who counselled the Nigerian government to be more serious in the trial of the defendants. The judge also extended similar counselling to the defence lawyers to stop using frivolous applications to delay the trial which was started in 2015. Meanwhile, Justice Nyako adjourned till March 17 for the resumption of the trial. 